row.Title: Five Years Of Recovery Haven’t Boosted The Median Household Income FiveThirtyEight » DataLab | FiveThirtyEight
row.Selection: The income of the median U.S. household was $51,900 in 2013, the Census Bureau reported Tuesday. That’s essentially unchanged from 2012, after adjusting for inflation, and is 8 percent lower than in 2007, before the recession began.
